## About {#about .section-heading}

::: {.bio-block}

<div class="bio-avatar-placeholder">LEW</div>

::: {}
I work at the intersection of data, law, and organizational decision-making.
My non-work work focuses on making rigorous analytical thinking accessible —
through unexpected datasets, honest methodology, and visualizations that
show their own uncertainty.

::: {.credential-badges}
<span class="badge-item">PhD — [Social Psychology, certificate in Research Methods and Data Analysis]</span>
<span class="badge-item">JD — [specialized in Health Law]</span>
<span class="badge-item">[Senior Research Associate / National Center for State Courts]</span>
:::

I'm particularly interested in the gap between how organizations say they
make decisions and how they actually make decisions — and in the role
that poorly designed measurement plays in that gap.

When I'm not doing that, I'm building models of hip-hop artists.
:::

:::

