## What I do {.section-heading}

::: {.columns}

::: {.column width="33%"}
**Teaching**

Executive and graduate education in data storytelling, measurement design,
and evidence-based decision-making. I use real datasets with documented
flaws — because clean pedagogical data teaches the wrong lessons.
:::

::: {.column width="33%"}
**Research**

Applied work at the boundary of law, psychology, and data storytelling.
Particular interest in construct validity, uncertainty quantification,
and the politics of how metrics get built and used.
:::

::: {.column width="33%"}
**Projects**

Independent projects that translate methodological ideas into
interactive, shareable artifacts. The hip-hop table is one.
More in [the projects gallery](projects/index.html).
:::

:::

